cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about simultaneous translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine translation (MT), so cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces a new model that involves minor changes to the existing neural translation framework, which suggests that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Learning). The model is trained using neural networks, which is a common technique in NLP and MT, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions experiments on Chinese-to-English translation, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since computer vision and NLP are often combined in multilingual applications.
